Cookies are active), and `setCookie` (from `\\Slim\\Slim`) is called with `$time` (or `cookies.lifetime`) being a _string_, the serialization of the cookie (`\\Slim\\Http\\Util::serializeCookies`) sets the `$expires` argument of `\\Slim\\Http\\Util::encodeSecureCookie` as the string without parsing it with `strtotime`.\n\nThis causes the secure cookie value to have the expires string before the first `|` separator, instead of having a timestamp.\n\nWhen this cookie value reaches `\\Slim\\Http\\Util::decodeSecureCookie` it's not accepted when the (supposed) timestamp is checked against `time()`.\n\nI wrote a test for this, but it depends on `\\Slim\\Http\\Cookies` and `\\Slim\\Http\\Headers`: https://gist.github.com/shello/6026460\n","closed_by":{"login":"codeguy","id":31677,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNjc3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/31677?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy","html_url":"https://github.com/codeguy","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/codeguy/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/slimphp/Slim/issues/568/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/slimphp/Slim/issues/568/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}